<item>
            <title>[SPARK-23089] &quot;Unable to create operation log session directory&quot; when parent directory not present</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-23089</link>
                <project id="12315420" key="SPARK">Spark</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When creating a session directory, Thrift should create the parent directory &lt;em&gt;(i.e. /tmp/hive/operation_logs)&lt;/em&gt; if it is not present.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It&apos;s common for operators to clean-up old and empty directories in /tmp, or to have tools (systemd-tmpfiles or tmpwatch) that do it automatically.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This was fixed in &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HIVE-12262&quot; title=&quot;Session log dir cannot be created in some cases&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HIVE-12262&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HIVE-12262&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; but not in Spark Thrift as seen by this:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;18/01/15 14:22:49 WARN HiveSessionImpl: Unable to create operation log session directory: /tmp/hive/operation_logs/683a6318-adc4-42c4-b665-11dad14d7ec7&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Resolved by manually creating /tmp/hive/operation_logs/&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>&lt;p&gt;/usr/hdp/2.6.3.0-235/spark2/jars/spark-hive-thriftserver_2.11-2.2.0.2.6.3.0-235.jar&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;$ cat /etc/redhat-release&lt;br/&gt;
Red Hat Enterprise Linux Server release 7.4 (Maipo)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;$ ps aux|grep ^hive.*spark.*thrift&lt;br/&gt;
hive     1468503  0.9  0.5 13319628 1411676 ?    Sl   Jan15  10:18 /usr/java/default/bin/java -Dhdp.version=2.6.3.0-235 -cp /usr/hdp/current/spark2-thriftserver/conf/:/usr/hdp/current/spark2-thriftserver/jars/*:/usr/hdp/current/hadoop-client/conf/ -Xmx2048m org.apache.spark.deploy.SparkSubmit --properties-file /usr/hdp/current/spark2-thriftserver/conf/spark-thrift-sparkconf.conf --class org.apache.spark.sql.hive.thriftserver.HiveThriftServer2 --name Thrift JDBC/ODBC Server spark-internal&lt;/p&gt;</environment>
